---
description: 
alwaysApply: true
---

- The plots need to fit inside a conference paper format, so either they are as wide as 1 column or both columns in the paper (documentclass: conference, IEEEtran, LaTeX)
- All text in the plots need to be the same size as text in the paper, so make sure all text have same size
- Text need to be in LaTex fontstyle
- Plots need to be clear and visible: thick lines and dots, no small textures
- No titels inside the plots, they will be written above the figure in latex instead
- Always use kHz when plotting with bandwidth
- Always specify the unit for the axis
